{"ticker": "ATAI UQ", "company": "ATAIBECKLEY INC", "weight_sum": 1.55, "etfs": ["ARKG"], "is_private": false, "query": "($ATAI OR \"Ataibeckley\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since:2026-04-28 until:2026-04-29", "n_fetched": 5, "n_kept": 3, "n_dropped": 2, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2049140985620242880", "url": "https://x.com/C_Angermayer/status/2049140985620242880", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/C_Angermayer/status/2049140985620242880", "text": "Great piece from @Shea_ARK \n\n\"AtaiBeckley is advancing BPL-003\u2014an intra-nasal formulation derived from 5-MeO-DMT\u2014in treatment-resistant depression, with positive Phase 2b results supporting a Phase 3 initiation in the second quarter of 2026.[11] With FDA Breakthrough Therapy designation, BPL-003 has the potential to achieve fast-track review under the new Executive Order.\"\n\n\"Importantly, commercial viability for clinic-delivered mental health therapies is no longer speculative and could be ready to scale. Johnson & Johnson's Spravato is a ketamine-derived nasal spray that the FDA approved for TRD in 2019.[13] While it works through a different mechanism than classical psychedelics, Spravato not only created the playbook for clinic-administered, supervised-dosing that COMP360 and BPL-003 will follow, but also has proven its commercial potential with an annualized run rate of ~$1.9 billion.[14] COMP360 and BPL-003 are differentiated from Spravato on efficacy and dosing burden: Spravato requires twice-weekly, in-clinic dosing during the first four weeks and continued maintenance thereafter, while both Compass and AtaiBeckley\u2019s treatments might involve only one or two dosing sessions.\"\n\n$ATAI $CMPS", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 7, "replyCount": 2, "likeCount": 52, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 3845, "createdAt": "Tue Apr 28 14:57:36 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 8, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049140985620242880", "displayTextRange